href="jms-00AD.xml"
addr="jms-00AD"
title="Phoa’s principle">Phoa axiom</fr:link> in synthetic domain theory be deduced from <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-008T.xml"
addr="jms-008T"
title="Synthetic quasicoherence">synthetic quasicoherence</fr:link>? I believe that Paul Taylor may have commented on something in this direction once in MathOverflow, but I do not know if anyone has proved this. I think it could be an interesting test-case. In cases where we have a clean understanding of the geometric theory in question (as in simplicial sets), this might be feasible; but I wonder about more sophisticated models of synthetic domain theory.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
